WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.319 --> 00:00:10.790
Ode to the Columbia River: because you gave
us power

00:00:10.790 --> 00:00:13.219
How America’s most powerful river fuels
hope

00:00:13.219 --> 00:00:16.349
TEXT: With a flip of a switch, everything
changed

00:00:16.349 --> 00:00:20.200
FDR at Bonneville Dam Dedication: “In the
construction of this dam”

00:00:20.200 --> 00:00:25.550
TEXT: Since1937,
FDR: “we have had our eyes on the future

00:00:25.550 --> 00:00:28.539
of the nation”
TEXT: You brought electricity to the rural

00:00:28.539 --> 00:00:31.179
Northwest
FDR: “the cheapening of electric power”

00:00:31.179 --> 00:00:37.030
TEXT: You broke down barriers for families
burdened

00:00:37.030 --> 00:00:42.079
FDR: “and the distribution of that power”
TEXT: By daily chores

00:00:42.079 --> 00:00:55.109
You gave us light, even at night
FDR: “Its cost will be returned to the United

00:00:55.109 --> 00:00:59.190
States, many, many times over.”

00:00:59.190 --> 00:01:13.880
TEXT: With the flip of a switch you gave us
power,

00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:53.960
The power to win a world war,
The power to save others,

00:01:53.960 --> 00:02:24.019
The power to prosper,
Today, you are still giving.

00:02:24.019 --> 00:02:29.090
You water the crops that feed us.

00:02:29.090 --> 00:02:30.740
You open the doors for trade and commerce.

00:02:30.740 --> 00:02:31.740
You give us a place to play and to rest.

00:02:31.740 --> 00:02:32.740
Because of you we can breathe clean air.

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:33.740
Your carbon-free power even brews our best
beer.

00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:34.740
Your current is steadfast.

00:02:34.740 --> 00:02:35.740
Your cost is low.

00:02:35.740 --> 00:02:36.740
That’s what major industries know.

00:02:36.740 --> 00:02:37.740
We lead the nation linking wind
We renew because of you.

00:02:37.740 --> 00:02:38.740
News Report Audio: “It was a sad experience
for some; the Indians solemnly watched their

00:02:38.740 --> 00:02:39.740
ancient fishing grounds at Celilo Falls slowly
disappeared under the water.

00:02:39.740 --> 00:02:40.740
TEXT: We learned to listen, to mitigate, to
mend…

00:02:40.740 --> 00:02:41.740
Terry Goudy-Rambler, Yakama Nation: “It
brings tears, to know that we’re never,

00:02:41.740 --> 00:02:42.740
ever gonna have that, which it has been taken
from us: our way of life.”

00:02:42.740 --> 00:02:43.740
TEXT: To commit to the future
Terry Goudy-Rambler, Yakama Nation: “So

00:02:43.740 --> 00:02:44.740
I’m glad that we’re here with the inter
agencies.

00:02:44.740 --> 00:02:53.380
They are going to honor this day today, and
that we’ll choose to walk this way.

00:02:53.380 --> 00:02:56.280
Thank you.”

00:02:56.280 --> 00:03:05.760
TEXT: Together, we built one of the largest
ecosystem recovery efforts in the world.

00:03:05.760 --> 00:03:12.600
Employee: “It is really exciting to see
the project come to fruition.”

00:03:12.600 --> 00:03:18.299
TEXT: Oh, Columbia, because you give we give
to you

00:03:18.299 --> 00:03:23.650
We honor your bounty, together, with our partners,
As a global leader in saving energy

00:03:23.650 --> 00:03:24.650
We inspire our children to unlock your secrets
Oh, Columbia your raw power makes the most

00:03:24.650 --> 00:03:25.650
amazing energy, on earth.

00:03:25.650 --> 00:03:25.654
Thank you, mighty Columbia.

